(ELEVATOR DINGS)

03:37.499 --> 03:39.466
MAN: All right, I'll
get her in right away.

03:39.468 --> 03:40.467
MAN 2:
Appreciate it.

03:41.902 --> 03:43.803
Hi.
Hi.

03:43.805 --> 03:47.874
WOMAN (OVER PA): <i>Dr. Klyczynski to ER,
stat. Dr. Klyczynski to ER, stat.</i>

03:47.876 --> 03:50.410
Hi, excuse me.
Yeah, just a minute, okay?

03:52.447 --> 03:54.247
Fill this out for me
and wait over there.

03:54.249 --> 03:55.748
No, I'm... I'm Dr. Forster.

03:55.750 --> 03:57.551
I was told to report here.

03:57.553 --> 03:59.619
You'll be covering 22 patients
on rounds today,

03:59.621 --> 04:01.288
this floor and the next.

04:01.290 --> 04:03.123
Twenty-two?
Quiet morning.

04:03.125 --> 04:05.058
If you get into trouble,
beep me,

04:05.060 --> 04:06.393
but don't make it a habit.

04:06.395 --> 04:08.761
The med students
will help you out with scutwork.

04:08.763 --> 04:11.764
What's he doing here?
I ordered an MRI, stat.

04:11.766 --> 04:13.233
Transport said
about four hours.

04:13.235 --> 04:15.602
He could be dead in four hours.

04:15.604 --> 04:17.904
Never mind. Dr. Forster, MRI.

04:17.906 --> 04:19.800
That's a right, two
lefts, elevator to two.

04:19.826 --> 04:20.273
Okay.

04:20.274 --> 04:23.276
Follow the signs.
Hustle back here for rounds.

04:23.278 --> 04:24.777
Um, Dr. Kly...

04:26.981 --> 04:28.315
Are you taking me somewhere?

04:28.317 --> 04:30.650
I certainly hope so, sir.

04:30.652 --> 04:32.185
How are you feeling today?

04:32.187 --> 04:33.720
Am...? Am I gonna make it?

04:33.722 --> 04:35.155
Uh, yes.

04:35.157 --> 04:36.423
Absolutely.

04:36.425 --> 04:38.558
(SAW BLADE WHIRRING)

04:38.560 --> 04:40.527
(MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

04:40.529 --> 04:42.629
Alex!

04:42.631 --> 04:47.167
I made my famous spinach pie.
The trailer's nice and toasty.

04:47.169 --> 04:49.035
I can't.

04:51.539 --> 04:53.507
Look, it's really cold
out here.

04:53.509 --> 04:55.708
Don't get sick on me
or anything.

04:55.710 --> 04:57.043
I never get sick.

04:58.946 --> 05:00.147
So I heard you bought a house,

05:00.149 --> 05:03.350
and apparently
I'm the last one to know.

05:03.352 --> 05:04.984
I thought I mentioned that.

05:04.986 --> 05:07.354
Wait.

05:07.356 --> 05:08.855
Where?

05:08.857 --> 05:11.358
Outside of town.
Up the shore a little bit.

05:11.360 --> 05:13.260
Up the shore?
There's no houses...

05:13.262 --> 05:14.761
Oh, God.

05:14.763 --> 05:17.297
You don't mean that thing
with the stilts and the...?

05:17.299 --> 05:18.431
(WOMAN YELPS)

05:19.433 --> 05:20.433
You all right?

05:20.435 --> 05:21.801
Yeah.

05:21.803 --> 05:23.170
Are you crazy?

05:24.505 --> 05:27.407
Why would you take that house,
Alex?

05:27.409 --> 05:29.176
It's made of glass.
There's no privacy.

05:30.478 --> 05:32.045
Mona?
Huh?

05:32.047 --> 05:34.080
Get yourself some boots.

05:37.485 --> 05:39.786
ALEX:
Hey, Gonzalez!

05:39.788 --> 05:41.555
(MUMBLING)

05:42.856 --> 05:44.291
(GRUNTS)

05:44.293 --> 05:45.458
(WHISPERS)
Four-thirty.

05:45.460 --> 05:46.626
You lost?

05:46.628 --> 05:47.927
Yeah.

05:47.929 --> 05:49.896
Takes a while
to get your bearings.

05:49.898 --> 05:52.265
I'm Madhvi.
Kate Forster. Hi.

05:53.234 --> 05:55.001
Oh, wrong floor.

05:55.003 --> 05:56.869
Where'd you do your residency?

05:56.871 --> 05:59.472
Just a little community hospital
up on the North Shore.

05:59.474 --> 06:01.374
(♪)

06:20.394 --> 06:24.063
KATE: <i>Dear new tenant,
welcome to your new home.</i>

06:24.065 --> 06:26.032
<i>As the previous tenant,</i>
<i>let me say</i>

06:26.034 --> 06:29.168
<i>I hope you'll like living here</i>
<i>as much as I did.</i>

06:29.170 --> 06:32.472
<i>I filed the change of address</i>
<i>with the post office,</i>

06:32.474 --> 06:35.041
<i>but you know what a crapshoot</i>
<i>that can be.</i>

06:35.043 --> 06:36.309
<i>So if anything slips through,</i>

06:36.311 --> 06:38.911
<i>would you do me a favor</i>
<i>and forward my mail?</i>

06:38.913 --> 06:42.782
<i>I'd appreciate it.</i>
<i>My new address is below.</i>

06:42.784 --> 06:44.851
<i>Thanks in advance.</i>

06:44.853 --> 06:46.819
<i>P.S.</i>

06:46.821 --> 06:48.921
"Sorry about the paw prints
by the front door.

06:48.923 --> 06:51.791
"They were there
when I moved in.

06:51.793 --> 06:54.827
Same with the box in the attic."

06:56.664 --> 06:58.365
Paw prints?

06:58.367 --> 07:00.333
What the hell
is she talking about?

07:10.711 --> 07:12.011
(DOOR SHUTS)

07:15.015 --> 07:18.451
Hey, baby girl. Hi. Hi. Hey.

07:19.953 --> 07:20.953
(FLICKS SWITCH)

07:20.955 --> 07:22.489
(KEYS JINGLING)

07:29.597 --> 07:30.830
Fix the light.

07:32.700 --> 07:34.167
Get dog food, huh?

07:34.169 --> 07:35.868
(DOG BARKS)

07:35.870 --> 07:37.904
Get human food.

07:37.906 --> 07:39.939
(♪)

08:06.166 --> 08:07.800
Hey. Hey.

08:07.802 --> 08:09.335
(DOG BARKING)

08:14.674 --> 08:16.075
Hey, come here.

08:21.982 --> 08:24.083
(PEOPLE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

08:25.519 --> 08:28.388
KATE:
Sixty degrees on Valentine's Day.

08:28.390 --> 08:29.755
This can't be Chicago.

08:29.757 --> 08:32.191
KATE'S MOTHER:
The TV says it's global warming.

08:32.193 --> 08:36.294
The icebergs start melting,
water covers the earth.

08:36.297 --> 08:38.998
Thank God we won't
live to see it.

08:40.134 --> 08:41.200
KATE:
What's this?

08:41.202 --> 08:43.369
Hm? Oh.
That's nothing.

08:43.371 --> 08:44.770
It's one of your father's.

08:44.772 --> 08:47.073
Dostoyevsky?
Oh, yeah.

08:48.509 --> 08:51.944
It's about a guy
who breaks the neck

08:51.946 --> 08:55.081
of a poor woman with an axe

08:55.083 --> 08:57.850
and, so far, keeps wandering
around regretting it.

08:59.386 --> 09:00.486
Mm.

09:02.222 --> 09:03.889
This is good.

09:03.891 --> 09:06.259
Oh, yeah?
Yeah. It's really good.

09:07.327 --> 09:08.494
Mmm.

09:08.496 --> 09:09.728
MAN:
I'll meet you there.

09:09.730 --> 09:11.197
What are you thinking?

09:11.199 --> 09:13.232
WOMAN:
My folks are coming into town.

09:13.234 --> 09:15.101
Nothing.

09:15.103 --> 09:16.669
When your father passed away,

09:16.671 --> 09:19.405
it was hard.
It still is hard.

09:19.407 --> 09:21.474
Holding his books,

09:21.476 --> 09:25.278
I feel like he's
with me somehow.

09:25.280 --> 09:27.613
Knowing that he was once
on the same pages,

09:27.615 --> 09:29.748
reading the same words.

09:29.750 --> 09:31.050
(VEHICLE HONKING)

09:31.052 --> 09:32.051
(TIRES SQUEALING)

09:33.887 --> 09:35.688
KATE:
Dear God.

09:35.690 --> 09:38.023
WOMAN 2: Oh, my God!
Somebody call an ambulance!

09:38.025 --> 09:39.325
(PANICKED SHOUTING)

09:39.327 --> 09:41.227
We need an ambulance
at Daley Plaza.

09:41.229 --> 09:44.363
A man has been struck by a bus.
Get an EMT crew here. Sir...

09:44.365 --> 09:46.432
COP: Get out the street.
Get on the sidewalk.

09:46.434 --> 09:48.434
On the sidewalk. Off the street.
Sir? Sir?

09:48.436 --> 09:51.070
Get on the sidewalk!
Get on the sidewalk!

09:51.072 --> 09:55.040
ALEX: I'd like to get the foundation
on number 17 dug today.

09:55.042 --> 09:58.010
MULHERN: Look, I know you're
kind of new around here, kid.

09:58.012 --> 09:59.845
What?

09:59.847 --> 10:03.182
I can't get to 17 until
at least next week.

10:03.184 --> 10:06.385
Come on, Mulhern.
That's bullshit and you know it.

10:06.387 --> 10:08.887
Take Clemens and Rodriguez
off of roofing.

10:08.889 --> 10:11.790
Jorge can run the backhoe
they're not using on 14,

10:11.792 --> 10:13.692
and grab four or five
of those other guys

10:13.694 --> 10:16.662
who are sitting around
doing nothin' on seven and 10.

10:16.664 --> 10:18.598
Paulie, Carlos, Frank, Danny,

10:18.600 --> 10:20.466
and what's-his-name,
the tall guy.

10:20.468 --> 10:23.169
Rafael.
Rafael.

10:23.171 --> 10:25.771
Let's go.
Okay.

10:25.773 --> 10:27.106
MAN 1: Ready?
MAN 2: Yeah.

10:27.108 --> 10:29.275
MAN 3: All I need's a 10 and 11.
(WHISTLES SHARPLY)

10:29.277 --> 10:30.309
Hey!

10:33.847 --> 10:36.915
WOMAN (OVER PA): <i>Housekeeping ER
to the Suture Room, please.</i>

10:36.917 --> 10:39.519
<i>Housekeeping ER</i>
<i>to the Suture Room.</i>

10:43.357 --> 10:46.225
Hey.
Hi.

10:46.227 --> 10:49.928
I heard about Daley Plaza.
Mm-hm.

10:49.930 --> 10:52.565
EMT said you fought hard
for the guy.

10:52.567 --> 10:56.369
Mm-hm. Yep.
Really knocked myself out.

10:56.371 --> 11:00.939
KLYCZYNSKI: <i>Kate, I'm going to tell
you what I tell every young doctor.</i>

11:00.941 --> 11:02.908
<i>Hopefully,</i>
<i>you'll be the first to listen.</i>

11:04.678 --> 11:05.978
<i>On your day off,</i>

11:05.980 --> 11:10.049
<i>get as far away</i>
<i>from this place as you can.</i>

11:10.051 --> 11:13.786
<i>Go someplace where you feel...</i>
<i>most like yourself.</i>

11:13.788 --> 11:16.556
(♪)

11:31.071 --> 11:33.138
(DOG PANTING)

11:36.142 --> 11:37.443
(DOG WHIMPERS)

12:10.043 --> 12:11.644
ALEX:
<i>Dear Ms. Forster:</i>

12:12.546 --> 12:14.113
<i>I got your note,</i>

12:14.115 --> 12:17.383
<i>and I'm afraid there must be</i>
<i>some kind of misunderstanding.</i>

12:17.385 --> 12:18.784
<i>As far as I know,</i>

12:18.786 --> 12:21.754
<i>the lake house has been empty</i>
<i>for several years.</i>

12:21.756 --> 12:23.389
<i>Maybe your note was intended</i>

12:23.391 --> 12:25.491
<i>for the Sandburg house</i>
<i>down the shore...</i>

12:25.493 --> 12:29.995
"... since no one has lived
in this house for years.

12:29.997 --> 12:33.132
But I'm curious
about the paw prints."

12:38.872 --> 12:40.306
KATE:
<i>Dear Mr. Wyler,</i>

12:40.308 --> 12:42.308
<i>I'm very familiar</i>
<i>with the Sandburg cottage,</i>

12:42.310 --> 12:44.977
<i>and I can guarantee</i>
<i>I never lived there.</i>

12:44.979 --> 12:45.978
<i>I'm old-fashioned,</i>

12:45.980 --> 12:47.079
<i>but I don't think a cottage</i>

12:47.081 --> 12:49.014
<i>should be over</i>
<i>6000 square feet.</i>

12:49.016 --> 12:51.183
<i>So let me try again.</i>

12:51.185 --> 12:53.118
<i>I used to live</i>
<i>at the lake house.</i>

12:53.120 --> 12:54.553
<i>Then I moved.</i>

12:54.555 --> 12:58.424
<i>Now I live at 1620 North Racine</i>
<i>in Chicago.</i>

12:58.426 --> 13:01.661
<i>I'd appreciate it if you would</i>
<i>forward my mail if you get any.</i>

13:01.663 --> 13:05.531
<i>Oh, by the way, it's 2006.</i>

13:05.533 --> 13:06.899
<i>Has been all year.</i>
<i>Ask anyone.</i>

13:08.468 --> 13:11.504
2006?

13:11.506 --> 13:13.906
What does she mean, 2006?

13:13.908 --> 13:16.241
God.

13:16.777 --> 13:17.777
Oh, God.

13:20.747 --> 13:23.248
MAN: Good morning, Mr. Wyler.
WOMAN: Morning, Mr. Wyler.

13:23.250 --> 13:24.984
ALL: Morning, sir.
Morning, morning.

13:24.986 --> 13:26.185
Hello, Mr. Wyler.

13:27.253 --> 13:28.688
Mr. Wyler.

13:30.023 --> 13:31.190
Sir.

13:34.160 --> 13:35.561
Well, uh...

13:35.563 --> 13:37.530
obviously I derive
my inspiration

13:37.532 --> 13:39.899
for the metaphor
of the fugue, the loop...

13:42.603 --> 13:44.003
Yeah.

13:56.249 --> 13:58.450
(HUMMING)

14:03.790 --> 14:05.791
HENRY: Two hours of that shit.
You kidding me?

14:05.793 --> 14:08.193
WOMAN: What are you talking about?
He didn't say a word.

14:08.195 --> 14:12.364
Sadistic, bitter,
bitter old man.

14:12.366 --> 14:15.300
I think you're being
a little overdramatic.

14:19.139 --> 14:20.940
Where are you going?

14:29.750 --> 14:30.950
MAN:
Oh, I love that place.

14:53.440 --> 14:56.275
I can't believe that thing's
still running.

14:59.279 --> 15:00.913
Yep.

15:01.915 --> 15:03.716
You look like shit.

15:03.718 --> 15:06.318
I missed you too.

15:07.153 --> 15:09.154
(CHUCKLES)

15:25.105 --> 15:26.806
Hey, forget about him.

15:31.812 --> 15:32.845
ALEX:
Condos.

15:32.847 --> 15:33.846
Riviera Estates.

15:33.848 --> 15:34.847
You're joking.

15:34.849 --> 15:36.082
I don't believe this.

15:36.084 --> 15:38.117
I come back after four years,

15:38.119 --> 15:40.086
and I get this in front of me.
What?

15:40.088 --> 15:42.454
My little brother thinking
he's Frank Lloyd Whatever.

15:42.456 --> 15:43.455
Oh, come on.

15:43.457 --> 15:44.957
Dad keeps you hostage

15:44.959 --> 15:46.759
in that little mythmaking
factory of his,

15:46.761 --> 15:49.862
while you haven't built
so much as a phone booth

15:49.864 --> 15:51.030
or a hamster cage.

15:51.032 --> 15:52.598
That's funny you say that,
actually.

15:52.600 --> 15:55.968
I have a hamster cage in mind.
A development of them, actually.

15:55.970 --> 15:58.137
Ah.
Prefab, no foundations.

15:58.139 --> 15:59.605
What do you think about that?

15:59.607 --> 16:01.173
See, that's what
I'm talking about.

16:01.175 --> 16:03.909
You have vision.
Ah.

16:03.911 --> 16:05.911
Speaking of which,

16:05.913 --> 16:09.348
I'd like you to know...
I bought a house.

16:09.350 --> 16:11.617
Where?
On the lake.

16:11.619 --> 16:13.919
You bought a lake house.
So you are making some money.

16:13.921 --> 16:16.188
Well, it's a dump.
Been abandoned for years, but...

16:16.190 --> 16:19.025
Oh, so you got an abandoned,
haunted lake hou...

16:19.027 --> 16:20.926
I guess... Yeah,
that's as good a reason as any

16:20.928 --> 16:23.929
for selling out and joining
the flabby-developers' guild.

16:23.931 --> 16:26.666
How about this?
I even got a dog.

16:26.668 --> 16:28.500
You got a dog?

16:28.502 --> 16:33.739
He just showed up at the house,
from out of nowhere.

16:33.741 --> 16:35.307
(CARLA BRUNI'S "LA NOYÉE"
PLAYING)

16:35.309 --> 16:42.014
<i>♪ Ou bien</i>
<i>Frôlant quelques ronces ♪</i>

16:42.016 --> 16:45.184
<i>♪</i> Tu hésites
<i>Et tu m'attends... ♪</i>

16:45.186 --> 16:46.518
HENRY:
What are we doing here?

16:46.520 --> 16:48.220
ALEX:
I have to deliver a letter.

16:48.222 --> 16:52.658
It should be here.
1620 North Racine.

16:55.996 --> 16:57.663
HENRY:
But...

16:58.999 --> 17:00.332
there's nothin' here.

17:00.334 --> 17:06.038
Are we meeting someone?
Does somebody live here? What?

17:06.040 --> 17:07.973
Yeah.

17:07.974 --> 17:10.474
I thought so.

17:10.477 --> 17:11.877
HENRY:
Should we ring the bell?

17:14.214 --> 17:16.848
(MAKES BUZZER SOUND)

17:30.763 --> 17:32.664
ALEX:
<i>Dear Ms. Forster:</i>

17:32.666 --> 17:36.468
<i>I went to 1620 North Racine,</i>
<i>and it's not there.</i>

17:36.470 --> 17:39.004
<i>It's just a construction site.</i>

17:39.006 --> 17:40.539
<i>From the pictures</i>
<i>it looks nice,</i>

17:40.541 --> 17:43.275
<i>but not for another 18 months.</i>

17:43.277 --> 17:45.444
<i>What am I missing here?</i>

17:45.446 --> 17:46.878
<i>Maybe you got</i>
<i>the address wrong,</i>

17:46.880 --> 17:49.181
<i>because I noticed</i>
<i>you got the date wrong too.</i>

17:49.183 --> 17:52.851
You really
wanna play this game.

17:52.853 --> 17:57.122
If you are truly
in the year 2004,

17:58.858 --> 18:01.160
then...

18:03.430 --> 18:05.530
be forewarned.

18:07.267 --> 18:08.600
Remember that day?

18:08.602 --> 18:11.736
You were not happy.
Remember that?

18:11.738 --> 18:12.838
(SIGHS)

18:12.840 --> 18:14.306
I know.

18:14.308 --> 18:17.943
KATE: <i>Okay, my mystery
correspondent, I get it.</i>

18:17.945 --> 18:19.511
<i>Just in case you really are</i>

18:19.513 --> 18:21.546
<i>where and when</i>
<i>you think you are,</i>

18:21.548 --> 18:23.315
<i>you'll need this.</i>

18:23.317 --> 18:25.417
<i>There was a freak late snow</i>
<i>that spring</i>

18:25.419 --> 18:26.818
<i>and everyone got sick.</i>

18:26.820 --> 18:30.456
<i>So plenty of rest,</i>
<i>lots of fluids.</i>

18:30.458 --> 18:31.790
<i>Doctor's orders.</i>
(SCOFFS)

18:31.792 --> 18:34.559
Snow. Right.

18:39.232 --> 18:42.201
Yeah, come to papa.

18:48.941 --> 18:51.543
(WIND WHISTLING)

19:04.491 --> 19:05.924
(SNEEZES)

19:11.531 --> 19:13.534
(♪)

20:18.498 --> 20:20.232
KATE:
Jackie.

20:21.401 --> 20:23.569
Jack.
(JACK BARKING)

20:23.571 --> 20:26.771
Jack, come on. Come on, girl.
Come on, come on. Jack.

20:34.447 --> 20:35.547
(BARKING)

20:44.591 --> 20:46.925
(BARKING)

21:12.985 --> 21:16.555
"Impossible, I know.
Not possible...

21:16.557 --> 21:18.557
but it's happening."

21:28.934 --> 21:31.236
Okay.

21:31.238 --> 21:32.538
(SIGHS)

21:34.974 --> 21:36.441
Where am I?

21:36.443 --> 21:37.576
(SNIFFS)

21:39.712 --> 21:40.712
(SIGHS)

21:41.481 --> 21:43.615
Very clever.

21:45.618 --> 21:48.086
"The lake house."

21:48.088 --> 21:49.854
The lake house.
Yes, well, as you can see,

21:49.856 --> 21:51.256
I, too, am at the lake house,

21:51.258 --> 21:52.824
but I'm getting
tired of these games

21:52.826 --> 21:54.593
so I'm leaving, okay? Bye.

21:54.595 --> 21:55.894
Thank you. Bye.

21:58.398 --> 22:01.600
Maybe we should
introduce ourselves properly.

22:06.272 --> 22:09.708
KATE: <i>I'm a doctor, dedicated
to curing the sick.</i>

22:09.710 --> 22:12.311
(SPRAYS)
<i>At least, trying to.</i>

22:12.313 --> 22:15.914
ALEX: <i>I'm an architect.
I like to build.</i>

22:15.916 --> 22:18.950
<i>And while I wouldn't say</i>
<i>my current project is ideal,</i>

22:18.952 --> 22:21.553
<i>it allows me to be here,</i>
<i>in this place,</i>

22:21.555 --> 22:24.289
<i>and that's enough for now.</i>
(TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

22:24.291 --> 22:25.790
<i>But tell me something.</i>

22:25.792 --> 22:28.527
<i>If you're working</i>
<i>in a hospital in Chicago now,</i>

22:28.529 --> 22:30.395
<i>where were you before,</i>
<i>in my time?</i>

22:32.232 --> 22:34.065
KATE:
<i>Two years ago, in your time,</i>

22:34.067 --> 22:37.035
<i>I was working in internal</i>
<i>medicine in Madison.</i>

22:37.037 --> 22:39.738
(ALARM BEEPING)

22:41.207 --> 22:43.508
ALEX:
<i>Tell me about the future.</i>

22:43.510 --> 22:45.277
<i>What's it like</i>
<i>in the year 2006?</i>

22:47.113 --> 22:51.516
KATE: <i>Hm. I'm afraid the
world's pretty much the same.</i>

22:51.518 --> 22:53.852
<i>Of course, we all dress</i>
<i>in shiny metal jump suits</i>

22:53.854 --> 22:56.688
<i>and drive flying cars,</i>
<i>and no one talks anymore</i>

22:56.690 --> 22:58.423
<i>because we can</i>
<i>read each other's minds.</i>

22:58.425 --> 22:59.658
<i>(CHUCKLES)</i>

22:59.660 --> 23:02.994
<i>But the truth is,</i>
<i>man from the past,</i>

23:02.996 --> 23:05.364
<i>not much</i>
<i>has really changed in 2006.</i>

23:05.366 --> 23:08.267
(JACK BARKING)

23:08.269 --> 23:09.901
KATE:
<i>Speaking of the past, though,</i>

23:09.903 --> 23:12.237
<i>I've been thinking about</i>
<i>the paw prints.</i>

23:12.239 --> 23:13.505
<i>How is that possible?</i>

23:13.507 --> 23:16.541
Well, I think
we have the same dog.

23:16.543 --> 23:19.978
KATE: <i>Oh, yeah?
What's yours like?</i>

23:19.980 --> 23:23.582
<i>According to the vet, mine</i>
<i>is 8 years old, in my time.</i>

23:23.584 --> 23:24.716
<i>Uh, 6 in yours.</i>

23:26.486 --> 23:28.887
<i>She's skinny, has sad eyes,</i>

23:28.889 --> 23:32.190
<i>snores...</i>
<i>and sleeps like a person.</i>

23:32.192 --> 23:34.693
<i>I don't know why,</i>
<i>but I call her Jack.</i>

23:34.695 --> 23:36.695
Hello, Jack.

23:39.865 --> 23:42.701
ALICIA (OVER TV):
<i>It's nice out here.</i>

23:42.703 --> 23:46.004
<i>Let's not go out for dinner.</i>
<i>Let's stay here.</i>

23:46.006 --> 23:47.072
Hey.

23:47.074 --> 23:48.474
DEVLIN (OVER TV):
<i>We have to eat.</i>

23:48.476 --> 23:50.709
What are you doing?
You're supposed to be asleep.

23:50.711 --> 23:51.710
<i>I'll cook.</i>

23:53.379 --> 23:54.879
<i>I thought</i>
<i>you didn't like to cook.</i>

23:56.216 --> 23:58.617
<i>No, I don't like to cook.</i>

23:58.619 --> 24:00.819
GIRL:
Is she gonna marry him?

24:00.821 --> 24:01.987
What do you think?

24:01.989 --> 24:04.556
I don't know.
He's kind of old.

24:04.558 --> 24:05.690
(CHUCKLES)

24:05.692 --> 24:08.393
Okay, he's not that old.

24:08.395 --> 24:10.395
My mom's
last boyfriend was bald.

24:10.397 --> 24:12.498
He was nice,

24:12.500 --> 24:14.500
but my mom didn't marry him.

24:14.502 --> 24:16.435
No?
"There's always somethin' better

24:16.437 --> 24:18.604
comin' around the corner."

24:18.606 --> 24:21.406
That's what she says.

24:21.408 --> 24:24.243
Maybe that's
what that lady should do.

24:24.245 --> 24:26.578
Wait for something better
to come around the corner.

24:26.580 --> 24:28.147
Maybe.

24:30.150 --> 24:31.517
But if she's not careful,

24:31.519 --> 24:34.453
she could spend
her whole life waiting.

24:34.455 --> 24:37.289
<i>Do you want me to bring</i>
<i>anything back with me?</i>

24:37.291 --> 24:40.759
<i>Yes. What about</i>
<i>a nice bottle of wine</i>

24:40.761 --> 24:42.561
<i>to celebrate?</i>

24:42.563 --> 24:45.797
<i>What time shall I come back?</i>
<i>Seven o'clock.</i>

24:45.799 --> 24:48.767
KATE: <i>Sorry I haven't made
it to the mailbox lately.</i>

24:48.769 --> 24:52.971
<i>It's been a long week.</i>
<i>All night shifts.</i>

24:52.973 --> 24:56.041
ALEX: <i>Good to hear from you.
I thought you left me.</i>

24:56.043 --> 24:58.143
<i>You should know that</i>
<i>you're my only connection</i>

24:58.145 --> 25:00.646
<i>to the future.</i>

25:00.648 --> 25:03.282
<i>How come we never talk</i>
<i>about the things we like?</i>

25:03.284 --> 25:07.952
KATE: <i>Hm. Well, let's see.
Reading the classics to Jack.</i>

25:07.954 --> 25:09.221
ALEX:
<i>Who's his favorite?</i>

25:09.223 --> 25:11.290
KATE:
<i>Dostoyevsky.</i>

25:11.292 --> 25:13.692
ALEX:
<i>For me, this city,</i>

25:13.694 --> 25:15.160
<i>on a day when</i>
<i>the light is so clear</i>

25:15.162 --> 25:16.995
<i>that I can touch every detail,</i>

25:16.997 --> 25:19.864
<i>every brick and window</i>
<i>in the buildings I love.</i>

25:19.866 --> 25:24.035
<i>Come on, take a walk with me,</i>
<i>this Saturday. Let me show you.</i>

25:24.037 --> 25:26.205
KATE:
<i>You're crazy.</i>

25:26.207 --> 25:28.307
<i>Why are you going through</i>
<i>all this trouble for me?</i>

25:28.309 --> 25:30.875
ALEX: <i>No trouble.
Summer's here.</i>

25:30.877 --> 25:32.143
(EELS' "ANT FARM" PLAYING)

25:32.145 --> 25:35.714
<i>♪ Walk down the street</i>
<i>I'm thinking ♪</i>

25:35.716 --> 25:38.016
<i>♪ Everybody move along</i>

25:38.018 --> 25:43.988
<i>♪ I've got a sad-hearted</i>
<i>Needing to belong ♪</i>

25:43.990 --> 25:47.859
ALEX: <i>Okay, your turn.
Favorite things.</i>

25:47.861 --> 25:50.895
KATE:
<i>Where to start? Okay.</i>

25:50.897 --> 25:54.199
<i>When I smell the flowers</i>
<i>before I see them.</i>

25:54.201 --> 25:58.704
<i>When it starts to rain</i>
<i>just as the picnic is ending.</i>

25:58.706 --> 26:02.774
<i>And I love the smell</i>
<i>of Jack's paws.</i>

26:02.776 --> 26:05.611
ALEX: <i>You didn't forget to
mention your husband, did you?</i>

26:05.613 --> 26:08.447
KATE: <i>Oh. Well, of course
I love my husband,</i>

26:08.449 --> 26:10.081
<i>who is also a doctor.</i>

26:10.083 --> 26:12.718
<i>Plastic surgeon</i>
<i>for small farm animals.</i>

26:12.720 --> 26:15.220
ALEX:
<i>Good. I'm married too.</i>

26:15.222 --> 26:18.890
<i>I've got eight children,</i>
<i>and none of them look like me.</i>

26:18.892 --> 26:20.191
<i>I'm worried, Kate.</i>

26:20.193 --> 26:22.461
KATE: <i>I would be too.</i>
<i>(ALEX CHUCKLES)</i>

26:22.463 --> 26:24.696
ALEX:
<i>I'm single.</i>

26:24.698 --> 26:26.465
KATE:
<i>Me too.</i>

26:26.467 --> 26:29.468
<i>Oh. Wow.</i>

26:29.470 --> 26:31.570
<i>Number 27.</i>

26:31.572 --> 26:33.938
ALEX: <i>She's a beauty.
My father used to tell me</i>

26:33.940 --> 26:37.041
<i>she was the grandma</i>
<i>for all the houses in the city.</i>

26:37.043 --> 26:40.312
<i>He used to take me on walks</i>
<i>like I'm taking you now.</i>

26:41.414 --> 26:42.748
KATE:
<i>Alex?</i>

26:42.750 --> 26:44.383
ALEX:
<i>Kate?</i>

26:44.385 --> 26:47.218
KATE: <i>I wish we could have
done this walk together.</i>

27:02.235 --> 27:04.402
So, what do you think?

27:04.404 --> 27:06.938
He sounds like a nice boy.

27:06.940 --> 27:09.907
Sounds like a nice boy.
Anything else?

27:09.909 --> 27:11.643
He has wonderful penmanship.

27:11.645 --> 27:13.378
Mother,

27:13.380 --> 27:14.879
look at the date on the letter.

27:14.881 --> 27:16.014
The date.

27:16.016 --> 27:17.749
Oh, you mean the time thing?
Yes.

27:17.751 --> 27:19.717
That's just a detail.
Just a detail?

27:23.523 --> 27:25.657
(SIGHS)

27:25.659 --> 27:29.427
(GERRY MULLIGAN'S "ALMOST LIKE
BEING IN LOVE" PLAYING)

27:29.429 --> 27:32.764
SIMON: About the, uh...
The other day, uh,

27:32.766 --> 27:37.969
it was not a good moment.
I was in a hell of a hurry.

27:37.971 --> 27:39.604
ALEX:
Of course.

27:41.006 --> 27:43.375
You've got some
nice pieces here.

27:43.377 --> 27:44.709
Oh, yeah.

27:44.711 --> 27:46.578
Music's fine, music helps.

27:46.580 --> 27:47.879
(CHUCKLES)

27:47.881 --> 27:51.115
It's like Nietzsche says:
"Life would be senseless..."

27:51.117 --> 27:53.951
"Without music."

27:53.953 --> 27:56.054
I guess I told you that, huh?

27:56.056 --> 27:57.689
Pour yourself a drink.

27:57.691 --> 28:01.159
Can you appreciate
a good wine by now?

28:01.161 --> 28:03.828
You bet.

28:03.830 --> 28:06.565
You know, you'll have to forgive
your father for being curious,

28:06.567 --> 28:10.702
but where have you been
all these years?

28:10.704 --> 28:13.104
I thought your Kerouac days
were behind you.

28:13.106 --> 28:14.972
(CHUCKLES)

28:14.974 --> 28:17.775
I'm sorry, what?
What?

28:19.011 --> 28:21.513
Oh, you can come up
if you like.

28:30.223 --> 28:31.956
What are you working on?

28:31.958 --> 28:35.327
Oh, I'm just...
I'm just remembering things.

28:35.329 --> 28:38.196
It's not such an easy job,
let me tell you.

28:38.198 --> 28:41.366
Nor is it particularly innocent,
in my case.

28:41.368 --> 28:44.802
Your father
is writing his memoirs.

28:46.439 --> 28:48.206
Are we in it?

28:48.208 --> 28:50.275
What do you think?
Do you wanna be?

28:51.176 --> 28:52.810
Do you?

28:52.812 --> 28:56.481
Of course. You were all
a part of your father's life.

28:57.916 --> 28:59.884
Why are you talking to me
in the third person?

28:59.886 --> 29:01.853
Well, I... I don't...

29:01.855 --> 29:04.021
Because I'm writing
about myself, I suppose.

29:04.023 --> 29:05.257
Why, doesn't it suit you?

29:08.060 --> 29:11.630
I thought you might like these.

29:13.466 --> 29:15.967
What are these? Something
you've been working on?

29:15.969 --> 29:19.036
No, they're...
They're yours.

29:19.038 --> 29:23.107
From a house I just bought
on the lake.

29:24.042 --> 29:25.243
Oh, yes, I heard.

29:25.245 --> 29:28.079
They said some sleazy
little condo developer

29:28.081 --> 29:30.382
had snapped it up.

29:30.384 --> 29:33.918
Oh, come on.
Indulge your father.

29:33.920 --> 29:37.021
Can't you take a little joke,
for God's sake?

29:37.023 --> 29:39.157
Come on.

29:39.159 --> 29:42.226
Tell me.
Where have you been?

29:42.228 --> 29:43.861
I really want to know.

29:43.863 --> 29:46.364
I was trying to forget you.

29:48.100 --> 29:50.802
Or forgive you.

29:51.771 --> 29:54.506
Did you succeed?

29:56.241 --> 29:58.009
No.

30:02.281 --> 30:05.717
Let me know if you need
any help remembering.

30:07.320 --> 30:11.155
Oh, yeah, I will.

30:11.157 --> 30:13.358
KATE: Charging 360.
Get 1 milligram of epi.

30:13.360 --> 30:14.992
Have 300 amio ready
in case we need it.

30:14.994 --> 30:18.330
All clear?
NURSE: Clear.

30:18.332 --> 30:19.798
(HEART MONITOR BEEPING)

30:19.800 --> 30:22.099
Hold compression,
start bagging.

30:22.101 --> 30:23.468
He's got a rhythm. Slow.

30:23.470 --> 30:24.736
Do we have a pulse with that?

30:24.738 --> 30:26.805
We got a pulse, thready.
It's getting stronger.

30:26.807 --> 30:28.540
KATE:
<i>Long days, these days.</i>

30:28.542 --> 30:31.476
<i>I just worked</i>
<i>30 hours straight.</i>

30:31.478 --> 30:34.178
<i>Every time</i>
<i>I stop to take a breath,</i>

30:34.180 --> 30:37.549
<i>I realize how isolated</i>
<i>I've let myself become.</i>

30:37.551 --> 30:42.620
<i>Believe me,</i>
<i>you can get a bit desperate.</i>

30:44.189 --> 30:46.858
That one?
Okay. There you go.

30:46.860 --> 30:51.128
Nice move.
Very nice. Nice.

30:53.699 --> 30:56.968
<i>It's not that I'm complaining.</i>
<i>I love my work.</i>

30:56.970 --> 31:01.506
<i>And our tour through Chicago</i>
<i>opened my eyes to its beauty.</i>

31:01.508 --> 31:04.642
<i>But my heart still misses</i>
<i>the lake house...</i>

31:04.644 --> 31:07.746
<i>and its trees.</i>

31:07.748 --> 31:10.648
<i>I miss those trees so much.</i>

31:10.650 --> 31:14.452
(BRAD MEHLDAU'S
"WHEN IT RAINS" PLAYING)

31:50.723 --> 31:52.223
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

31:59.965 --> 32:02.266
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

32:27.560 --> 32:31.362
ALEX: <i>Don't worry, Kate.
We'll be together in time.</i>

32:31.364 --> 32:32.597
<i>Even if we're far apart,</i>

32:32.599 --> 32:34.165
<i>I'll find a way</i>
<i>to be close to you</i>

32:34.167 --> 32:36.601
<i>and take care of you.</i>

32:39.972 --> 32:42.406
Oh, lu, lu, lu, lu.

32:42.408 --> 32:44.208
Katerina.

32:45.544 --> 32:47.745
Take this.

32:47.747 --> 32:49.047
You should eat more.

32:49.049 --> 32:50.781
You too skinny.
I'm not too skinny.

32:50.783 --> 32:53.284
Remember how you used to eat
when you were little?

32:53.286 --> 32:54.385
Chuga, chuga, chug, chug.

32:54.387 --> 32:56.087
With your hands.
Yes, I remember.

32:56.089 --> 32:59.257
Now, did you or did you not
write to each other?

32:59.259 --> 33:00.291
To your father?

33:00.293 --> 33:01.659
No, to Clark Gable.

33:01.661 --> 33:04.262
Yes, to Dad.

33:06.565 --> 33:08.432
I, uh...

33:10.870 --> 33:12.636
What, Mom?

33:12.638 --> 33:14.839
Before your father...

33:14.841 --> 33:17.441
Yeah?

33:17.443 --> 33:21.645
There was this boy.

33:23.482 --> 33:25.083
Did you love him?

33:25.085 --> 33:27.618
Yeah.

33:30.389 --> 33:32.891
Well...

33:32.893 --> 33:34.425
Why...? Why didn't you
marry him?

33:36.661 --> 33:39.830
So that you could ask me
this question someday.

33:41.300 --> 33:45.103
(♪)

33:50.910 --> 33:52.977
Looks smaller.

33:54.947 --> 33:57.181
Uh, when did he complete it?

33:58.217 --> 34:00.785
You weren't born yet,
and I was 8.

34:02.454 --> 34:05.489
God.

34:05.491 --> 34:07.658
Corbusier meets
Frank Lloyd Wright.

34:09.261 --> 34:11.295
You know, Dad played cards
with both of 'em.

34:13.331 --> 34:14.331
Sharing a joint.

34:14.333 --> 34:15.333
Yeah, well...

34:15.335 --> 34:17.402
(CHUCKLES)

34:17.404 --> 34:19.703
ALEX:
Can't swim.

34:19.705 --> 34:21.605
There should be a stairway
down to the water,

34:21.607 --> 34:23.440
a porch, a deck.

34:23.443 --> 34:26.643
Here, you're in a...
In a box.

34:26.646 --> 34:30.114
A glass box with a view
to everything that's around you,

34:30.116 --> 34:31.782
but you can't touch it.

34:31.784 --> 34:36.321
No interconnection between
you and what you're looking at.

34:36.322 --> 34:38.289
HENRY:
I don't know, you know.

34:38.291 --> 34:39.657
He's got this big maple growing

34:39.659 --> 34:41.059
right in the middle
of the house.

34:41.061 --> 34:42.360
Containment.

34:45.764 --> 34:49.467
Containment and control.

34:49.469 --> 34:51.235
(BOTH LAUGHING)

34:51.237 --> 34:55.873
This house is about ownership,
not connection.

34:55.875 --> 34:59.877
I mean, it's beautiful.
Seductive, even.

34:59.879 --> 35:02.847
But it's incomplete.

35:04.883 --> 35:06.351
It was all about him.

35:06.353 --> 35:08.652
(THUNDER CRASHING)

35:08.654 --> 35:11.055
Dad knew how to build
a house, not a home.

35:12.057 --> 35:13.424
But you know,

35:13.426 --> 35:16.594
I think he wants us to do
what he couldn't.

35:16.596 --> 35:19.930
But admitting that...

35:19.932 --> 35:24.335
would mean admitting that
he came up short in some way,

35:24.337 --> 35:26.404
that he could do more.

35:26.406 --> 35:28.672
And that tortures him.

35:29.808 --> 35:32.310
Do you remember
being here with Mom?

35:39.151 --> 35:41.219
I remember she tried
to make it work here...

35:42.488 --> 35:44.389
with us...

35:44.391 --> 35:46.590
with him.

35:48.727 --> 35:50.428
Hey, what about
Visionary Vanguard?

35:50.430 --> 35:51.529
What about it?

35:51.531 --> 35:53.231
Come on.

35:53.233 --> 35:55.099
You can't convince me
you're gonna be happy

35:55.101 --> 35:57.268
building these saltboxes
for tourists.

35:57.270 --> 36:00.204
Nobody's gonna admire you
for that.

36:00.206 --> 36:01.205
Admire me for that?

36:01.207 --> 36:03.307
Yeah, Visionary Vanguard.

36:03.309 --> 36:04.308
(LAUGHS)

36:04.310 --> 36:06.244
That's your idea.

36:06.246 --> 36:08.112
I can't.
But you can keep the name.

36:08.114 --> 36:10.614
No, come on.
It's gotta be you and me.

36:10.616 --> 36:13.584
Henry, I'm sorry,
I can't. I...

36:13.586 --> 36:15.319
I just, uh...

36:15.321 --> 36:16.320
What?

36:16.322 --> 36:18.556
I've got other plans.

36:18.558 --> 36:20.724
You have a girlfriend?

36:22.561 --> 36:24.395
Nah... Mm, no.

36:25.931 --> 36:27.698
What is that?
You hesitated.

36:27.700 --> 36:29.067
No, I didn't hesitate.

36:30.735 --> 36:33.271
Come on, man. I don't have...
I don't have any time for that.

36:34.606 --> 36:36.074
What does time
have to do with it?

36:37.609 --> 36:39.944
Oh, you're gonna think
I'm crazy.

36:44.750 --> 36:47.418
KATE:
<i>My dearest Mr. Wyler:</i>

36:47.420 --> 36:50.788
<i>Are you willing to play</i>
<i>a game with me?</i>

36:50.790 --> 36:52.023
<i>Two years ago today,</i>

36:52.025 --> 36:54.391
<i>I was taking the 145 train</i>
<i>to Madison</i>

36:54.393 --> 36:57.962
<i>from the Riverside station,</i>
<i>and I forgot something there.</i>

36:57.964 --> 37:00.965
<i>It was a gift from my father.</i>

37:00.967 --> 37:02.566
<i>If you find it,</i>

37:02.568 --> 37:04.969
<i>can you please put it</i>
<i>in the mailbox?</i>

37:05.804 --> 37:08.405
<i>It would mean a lot.</i>

37:08.407 --> 37:11.642
<i>Yours, Kate.</i>

37:27.392 --> 37:28.893
Final call for
the 5:46 to Madison.

37:28.895 --> 37:30.361
Do you really wanna know?
Come on.

37:30.363 --> 37:32.463
(BOTH GIGGLING)

37:32.465 --> 37:34.799
All aboard.
MAN: Okay.

37:44.810 --> 37:46.510
I'll call you.

37:53.652 --> 37:56.020
(♪)

38:01.426 --> 38:03.194
(TRAIN HORN BLARING)

38:27.820 --> 38:31.255
ALEX: <i>Kate, I found it.
I have it with me.</i>

38:31.257 --> 38:34.325
<i>One day I'll get it to you.</i>
<i>Trust me.</i>

38:34.327 --> 38:37.328
<i>I know how important
it is to you.</i>

38:38.596 --> 38:42.233
<i>You might not remember,</i>
<i>but we saw each other.</i>

38:42.235 --> 38:44.335
<i>At least, I saw you.</i>

38:45.570 --> 38:49.841
<i>You never told me</i>
<i>how beautiful you are.</i>

38:49.843 --> 38:52.676
KATE: <i>Well, maybe you
saw somebody else.</i>

38:52.678 --> 38:55.379
<i>That was a bad hair year</i>
<i>for me.</i>

38:55.381 --> 38:58.749
ALEX: <i>Long brown hair.
Gentle, unguarded eyes.</i>

38:58.751 --> 39:01.018
KATE:
<i>Okay, okay, okay, okay.</i>

39:01.020 --> 39:03.520
<i>You saw me.</i>

39:03.522 --> 39:05.289
<i>But I still don't know</i>
<i>what you look like.</i>

39:07.259 --> 39:10.928
ALEX: <i>Well, why don't we just
get together in the future,</i>

39:10.930 --> 39:14.565
<i>and you can let me know</i>
<i>what you think.</i>

39:14.567 --> 39:16.367
It's a date.

39:19.571 --> 39:21.272
Okay.

39:21.274 --> 39:26.911
Why don't you call me
July 10th, 2006, at...

39:26.913 --> 39:30.514
9:05 p.m.

39:30.516 --> 39:34.952
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

39:45.730 --> 39:46.730
Hello.

39:46.732 --> 39:48.299
MAN:
<i>Kate?</i>

39:48.301 --> 39:49.300
Yes.

39:49.302 --> 39:51.135
<i>It's Morgan.</i>

39:52.470 --> 39:54.038
(CLEARS THROAT)

39:54.040 --> 39:55.572
Morgan.

39:55.574 --> 39:56.974
<i>Yeah, I'm here, in Chicago.</i>

39:56.976 --> 39:58.943
<i>I came down for a meeting,</i>
<i>but it was canceled,</i>

39:58.945 --> 40:00.378
<i>so I thought</i>
<i>I'd give you a call.</i>

40:01.479 --> 40:03.547
MORGAN:
Hey, uh, have you eaten?

40:03.549 --> 40:04.548
No, but I'm not...

40:04.550 --> 40:05.716
Neither have I.

40:05.718 --> 40:07.551
I just realized
I'm totally starving.

40:07.553 --> 40:08.719
We could grab a quick bite.

40:08.721 --> 40:09.987
Okay.

40:09.989 --> 40:10.988
Yeah?

40:10.990 --> 40:12.423
All right.

40:12.425 --> 40:13.424
MAN:
Hey, wait up.

40:13.426 --> 40:15.559
WOMAN:
Watch out, man.

40:15.561 --> 40:17.094
MAN:
All right.

40:17.096 --> 40:18.629
Looks pretty good.
Oh.

40:18.631 --> 40:19.696
Perfect.

40:19.698 --> 40:21.498
No, Morgan, it's...
It's not.

40:21.500 --> 40:22.566
No, no, trust me.

40:22.568 --> 40:25.036
It's... Okay.

40:26.372 --> 40:27.372
Hi there.

40:27.374 --> 40:28.506
One sec.

40:28.508 --> 40:30.174
Could you hold on
for a moment, please?

40:30.176 --> 40:31.409
We'd love a table for two.

40:31.411 --> 40:32.710
The name?

40:32.712 --> 40:36.481
Oh, um... we don't...
We don't have a reservation.

40:36.483 --> 40:38.182
I'm sorry, sir, we're booked...

40:38.184 --> 40:39.550
until October.

40:40.686 --> 40:41.786
October?

40:43.822 --> 40:46.524
Well...

40:46.526 --> 40:48.693
I'll get back to you.

40:50.996 --> 40:51.996
That went well.

40:51.998 --> 40:53.197
(LAUGHING)

40:53.199 --> 40:55.466
It's no big deal.

40:57.269 --> 40:59.470
(SIGHS)

40:59.472 --> 41:00.905
Oh, come on, stop it.

41:00.907 --> 41:02.373
It's the best restaurant
in town.

41:02.375 --> 41:04.074
Nobody gets a table here.

41:04.076 --> 41:05.443
No, it's not that.

41:05.445 --> 41:07.712
Well, what is it?

41:11.216 --> 41:14.352
I didn't do this right.

41:14.354 --> 41:15.853
There wasn't a meeting,
was there?

41:15.855 --> 41:17.422
You'd see me
if there was no big deal.

41:17.424 --> 41:18.856
If it was just...
Mm-hm, ambush.

41:18.858 --> 41:21.793
You know, coffee,
and coffee can turn into dinner,

41:21.795 --> 41:22.893
and dinner can turn into...

41:22.895 --> 41:24.395
Turn into what?

41:24.397 --> 41:26.864
I'll admit, I do sometimes get
a few steps ahead of myself.

41:26.866 --> 41:28.032
Morgan, a few steps?

41:28.034 --> 41:32.069
You're always leaping...
10 steps ahead.

41:33.305 --> 41:35.573
We were dating, what, a week?

41:35.575 --> 41:38.609
And you had our entire future
mapped out for us?

41:38.611 --> 41:40.010
Still in my residency,

41:40.012 --> 41:41.479
you were picking out
real estate.

41:41.481 --> 41:43.180
I would go to your house
for the weekend,

41:43.182 --> 41:46.217
you'd have the entire town
in your house to meet me.

41:46.219 --> 41:48.152
You know, I do seem
to remember that

41:48.154 --> 41:50.555
you made pretty fast friends
with one of them.

41:50.557 --> 41:52.022
What are you talking about?

41:52.024 --> 41:53.591
Oh, you know
what I'm talking about.

41:53.593 --> 41:54.792
That guy.
What guy?

41:54.794 --> 41:56.627
The guy I caught you
making out with.

41:56.629 --> 41:58.195
I wasn't making out with him.

41:58.197 --> 41:59.230
What, are we in...

41:59.232 --> 42:00.765
junior high school right now?

42:00.767 --> 42:02.967
What do you call it, then?

42:02.969 --> 42:05.770
A kiss.

42:05.772 --> 42:10.040
It was just one kiss
with some random guy that just...

42:10.042 --> 42:11.476
Years... You know what?

42:11.478 --> 42:13.310
Gentlemen...

42:13.312 --> 42:17.749
unit 381 on Riviera Estates
is complete.

42:17.751 --> 42:19.751
(ALL CHEERING)

42:19.753 --> 42:22.620
Congratulations.
You did a good job.

42:23.321 --> 42:24.756
Ah.

42:24.758 --> 42:25.757
One down...

42:25.759 --> 42:27.792
Forty-four to go.

42:27.794 --> 42:29.594
We're not terrifyingly
behind schedule,

42:29.596 --> 42:31.328
just alarmingly.

42:31.330 --> 42:33.063
(SIGHS)
It's gonna be okay.

42:33.065 --> 42:35.400
The guys are getting
to know their job,

42:35.402 --> 42:37.334
but we could use
another backhoe.

42:37.336 --> 42:39.937
And the water on 14
needs to be resealed.

42:39.939 --> 42:41.272
Shut up.

42:41.274 --> 42:42.339
What?

42:42.341 --> 42:44.208
I'm kind of disappointed
in you.

42:44.210 --> 42:45.743
Why?

42:45.745 --> 42:48.245
Because you're supposed to be
on top of things around here.

42:48.247 --> 42:49.614
I thought I was.

42:49.616 --> 42:53.317
Well, you never noticed these.

42:53.319 --> 42:55.119
Don't you remember?
You told me to get 'em.

42:55.121 --> 42:56.654
Right, right.

42:56.656 --> 42:59.356
Wow. Not exactly
what I had in mind, but...

42:59.358 --> 43:01.358
You like 'em?

43:01.360 --> 43:02.627
I like them.

43:02.629 --> 43:04.361
I think we should go out.
Tonight.

43:04.363 --> 43:05.362
(JACK BARKING)

43:05.364 --> 43:07.264
If you're not doing any...

43:07.266 --> 43:09.767
Jack? Jack.

43:09.769 --> 43:11.135
Hey, Jack.

43:14.640 --> 43:15.840
Jack!

43:16.975 --> 43:19.376
Come on, Jack!

43:19.378 --> 43:21.145
Alex, wait for me!

43:22.748 --> 43:24.615
ALEX:
Jack!

43:28.687 --> 43:30.621
Jack!

43:31.289 --> 43:33.023
Jack!

43:44.169 --> 43:45.636
Jack!

43:49.240 --> 43:51.576
(JACK BARKING)

43:54.212 --> 43:55.212
Yours, I take it?

43:55.214 --> 43:58.315
Yeah. Yeah,
sorry. Thanks.

43:58.317 --> 43:59.684
Come here, Jack.

43:59.686 --> 44:01.385
What were you thinking,
huh, girl?

44:01.387 --> 44:02.920
What were you thinking?

44:02.922 --> 44:04.522
She's never run off
like that before.

44:04.524 --> 44:05.790
You gotta keep an eye on them.

44:05.792 --> 44:07.091
What's his name?

44:07.093 --> 44:08.392
Her. Jack.

44:08.394 --> 44:10.695
Jack. It's a good name
for a girl.

44:10.697 --> 44:12.563
I should get one like you
for my girlfriend.

44:12.565 --> 44:13.831
She loves dogs.

44:13.833 --> 44:15.265
Hey, have we met before?

44:15.267 --> 44:16.934
No, don't think so.

44:16.936 --> 44:18.402
Morgan Price.

44:18.404 --> 44:19.871
Alex Wyler.

44:19.873 --> 44:21.606
Hey, man, you need
a hand with this?

44:21.608 --> 44:22.807
MORGAN: Yeah.
ALEX: Okay.

44:22.809 --> 44:24.375
MORGAN:
Lived here long?

44:24.377 --> 44:26.644
ALEX: Just a few months.
I've got a place on the lake.

44:26.646 --> 44:28.345
The lake, really?
I've been thinking...

44:28.347 --> 44:30.047
Alex. Oh, good.

44:30.049 --> 44:32.016
(PANTING)
Thank God you found him.

44:32.018 --> 44:33.618
Yeah.

44:33.620 --> 44:35.820
Mona, Morgan.
Morgan, Mona.

44:35.822 --> 44:36.821
Well, hello.

44:36.823 --> 44:37.822
Hi.

44:37.824 --> 44:38.823
It's good to meet you.

44:38.825 --> 44:40.124
Nice to meet you too.

44:40.126 --> 44:41.158
Nice boots there.

44:41.160 --> 44:43.093
Listen, just so you don't think

44:43.095 --> 44:44.595
I'm gonna drink
all this by myself,

44:44.597 --> 44:46.864
I'm having a bunch of friends
over tonight for a party.

44:46.866 --> 44:48.866
You two are welcome to come.

44:50.201 --> 44:51.736
Oh, hey, Alex.

44:52.838 --> 44:54.906
Take my card.
I might be looking

44:54.908 --> 44:56.373
to rent a place
on the lake myself.

44:56.375 --> 44:57.408
Okay.

44:57.410 --> 44:58.509
It's Kate, my girlfriend,

44:58.511 --> 45:00.110
she's never really liked
this place,

45:00.112 --> 45:02.179
and I promised her we'd look
for something new

45:02.181 --> 45:04.715
once she finishes
her residency in Madison.

45:04.717 --> 45:05.917
So if you hear of anything...

45:08.253 --> 45:09.754
Sure. She's a doctor?

45:09.756 --> 45:11.221
Yeah.

45:12.490 --> 45:13.490
Alex.

45:20.432 --> 45:21.599
Great to meet you, Morgan.

45:21.601 --> 45:23.734
Great to meet you.
All right.

45:23.736 --> 45:25.770
(CAROLE KING'S
"IT'S TOO LATE" PLAYING)

45:25.772 --> 45:28.739
Hey, Morgan,
what time's that party at?

45:28.741 --> 45:32.009
Eight o'clock.
It's Kate's birthday.

45:34.245 --> 45:37.648
<i>♪ Stayed in bed all morning</i>
<i>Just to pass the time ♪</i>

45:37.650 --> 45:40.184
It's Kate birthday.
Come on, Jack.

45:40.186 --> 45:43.320
<i>♪ There's something wrong here</i>
<i>There can be no denyin' ♪</i>

45:43.322 --> 45:45.556
<i>♪ One of us is changin' ♪</i>

45:45.558 --> 45:49.526
<i>♪ Or maybe we've just</i>
<i>Stopped tryin' ♪</i>

45:52.163 --> 45:56.968
<i>♪ And it's too late, baby</i>
<i>Now it's too late ♪</i>

45:56.970 --> 46:02.172
<i>♪ Though we really did try</i>
<i>To make it ♪</i>

46:02.174 --> 46:07.979
<i>♪ Something inside has died</i>
<i>And I can't hide... ♪</i>

46:07.981 --> 46:09.179
Hi.
Hi.

46:09.181 --> 46:10.314
What can I get you?

46:10.316 --> 46:12.683
Glass of white wine, please.

46:20.592 --> 46:21.826
<i>♪ It used to be so easy</i>

46:21.828 --> 46:23.094
Thank you.
You're welcome.

46:23.096 --> 46:25.663
<i>♪ Living here with you</i>

46:25.665 --> 46:30.067
<i>♪ You were light and breezy</i>
<i>And I knew just what to do ♪</i>

46:30.069 --> 46:36.473
<i>♪ Now you look so unhappy</i>
<i>And I feel like a fool ♪</i>

46:38.644 --> 46:44.214
<i>♪ And it's too late, baby</i>
<i>Now it's too late ♪</i>

46:44.216 --> 46:47.251
According to most
accepted social norms,

46:47.253 --> 46:51.588
a person should not drink
alone after 10 p.m.,

46:51.590 --> 46:53.257
unless they have a good excuse.

46:53.259 --> 46:56.360
Mm.
What's yours?

46:56.362 --> 46:57.762
Gosh, don't have one.

46:57.764 --> 46:58.963
(GIGGLES)

46:58.965 --> 47:01.032
I do.

47:01.034 --> 47:04.334
My youngest left for college
this morning.

47:04.336 --> 47:06.370
Marie.

47:06.372 --> 47:09.940
One day she's splashing around
a wading pool in diapers.

47:09.942 --> 47:15.379
Then she's packing up a Volvo
and driving to California.

47:15.381 --> 47:19.016
I just hope she knows
what she's getting into.

47:19.018 --> 47:20.250
Don't tell me.

47:20.252 --> 47:22.720
Premed?
Bingo.

47:25.991 --> 47:27.391
Hey, how are you?
Good to see you.

47:27.393 --> 47:29.060
I'm well, thanks.

47:29.062 --> 47:31.261
I want you to meet
some friends of mine.

47:31.263 --> 47:34.165
Alex, Mona, this is the Wootch.

47:34.167 --> 47:36.000
Susan, Johnny.
Hi.

47:36.002 --> 47:37.467
Let's get you something
to drink.

47:37.469 --> 47:39.136
Come on. Back here.
Bar's back here.

47:39.138 --> 47:41.405
Come on.
Hey, this is Marjorie.

47:41.407 --> 47:43.808
Why didn't you mention
it was today?

47:43.810 --> 47:46.143
We would have had a cake
for you or something.

47:46.145 --> 47:48.245
Oh, it's just time passing.

47:48.247 --> 47:50.514
I hate making
a big deal out of it.

47:50.516 --> 47:53.050
You keep a lot to yourself.

47:53.052 --> 47:55.552
Nothing wrong with it.

47:55.554 --> 47:56.921
But I've sometimes wondered

47:56.923 --> 48:00.390
what else you have
in your life besides work.

48:00.392 --> 48:02.526
Family? Boyfriend?

48:02.528 --> 48:05.229
Well, I did. Once.

48:05.231 --> 48:08.265
<i>His name was Morgan.</i>

48:08.267 --> 48:09.533
<i>Morgan?</i>
<i>Mm-hm.</i>

48:09.535 --> 48:11.936
<i>Morgan.</i>
<i>That's a sexy name.</i>

48:11.938 --> 48:13.070
<i>(GIGGLES)</i>

48:15.173 --> 48:17.775
ALL:
Surprise!

48:17.777 --> 48:21.779
(LAUGHING AND CHATTERING)

48:21.781 --> 48:23.580
Happy birthday, Katie.

48:24.783 --> 48:26.183
WOMAN 1:
Happy birthday.

48:26.185 --> 48:28.585
MAN:
Happy birthday.

48:29.654 --> 48:32.522
WOMAN 2:
We got you.

48:32.524 --> 48:33.590
This is Kate, obviously.

48:33.592 --> 48:34.825
Hi, Kate.

48:40.198 --> 48:41.598
This is Alex and Mona.

48:42.367 --> 48:43.600
Hi.
Hi.

48:43.602 --> 48:45.502
This guy's gonna help us
find our lake house.

48:45.504 --> 48:46.536
Oh.
Right?

48:50.275 --> 48:51.809
You haven't had cake.

48:51.811 --> 48:54.378
KATE:
<i>Anyway, well, I ended it.</i>

48:54.380 --> 48:55.813
And I'm happy now,

48:55.815 --> 48:58.315
and it was
the right thing to do.

48:59.417 --> 49:02.920
So who is it you write to?

49:02.922 --> 49:04.155
I couldn't help...

49:04.157 --> 49:06.390
Every time you get
a break at the hospital,

49:06.392 --> 49:07.557
you're writing something.

49:07.559 --> 49:09.426
There is someone.

49:09.428 --> 49:11.395
It's kind of
a long-distance relationship.

49:13.131 --> 49:14.131
How did you meet?

49:14.133 --> 49:15.365
(LAUGHING)
We haven't.

49:15.367 --> 49:17.234
What?
No.

49:17.236 --> 49:18.435
The story of my life.

49:18.437 --> 49:19.503
You're kidding.

49:19.505 --> 49:22.239
Keep everything at a distance.

49:22.241 --> 49:24.608
Everyone.

49:24.610 --> 49:26.576
The man who was standing
right in front of me,

49:26.578 --> 49:29.346
the one that wanted to marry me,
him, I push away.

49:29.348 --> 49:31.148
I run from him.

49:31.150 --> 49:34.351
In the meantime, the...

49:34.353 --> 49:38.155
The one man I can never meet,

49:38.157 --> 49:42.193
him, I would like to give
my whole heart to.

49:44.362 --> 49:46.230
He must write one hell
of a letter.

49:46.232 --> 49:48.065
Mm-hm.

49:48.067 --> 49:49.366
It's nice.

49:51.669 --> 49:53.204
It's safe.

49:53.206 --> 49:55.672
Christ, he's in prison, isn't he?
No.

49:55.674 --> 49:57.341
You're one of those women,
aren't you?

49:57.343 --> 49:59.977
No. No, he's just a guy
who lives on a lake.

49:59.979 --> 50:01.946
He's an architect.

50:10.889 --> 50:12.890
(♪)

50:25.436 --> 50:27.471
(WHISPERS)
Oh, my God.

50:27.473 --> 50:29.205
(DOOR SLAMS)

50:32.176 --> 50:33.276
(SIGHS)

50:33.278 --> 50:34.845
ALEX:
Happy birthday.

50:37.114 --> 50:39.616
Thank you.

50:39.618 --> 50:41.317
I hope it's a great year
for you.

50:41.319 --> 50:42.686
Thank you.

50:45.256 --> 50:48.124
I'm Alex.

50:48.126 --> 50:49.626
The lake-house guy.

50:49.628 --> 50:51.795
Oh, yeah.
How you doin'?

51:04.842 --> 51:06.309
May I?

51:13.585 --> 51:14.818
So you're gonna...

51:14.820 --> 51:17.020
You're gonna find us a place
on the lake, huh?

51:17.022 --> 51:18.521
I hope so.
Yeah.

51:18.523 --> 51:20.090
If I can.

51:20.092 --> 51:22.158
You're a real-estate
agent?

51:22.160 --> 51:23.359
No, I...

51:23.361 --> 51:26.196
I just, uh, have a lake house.

51:26.198 --> 51:28.599
Oh. Is it nice?

51:28.601 --> 51:30.433
Yeah, you'll love it.

51:30.435 --> 51:32.268
You're gonna rent it
after I move out.

51:32.270 --> 51:33.604
Oh, really?

51:38.375 --> 51:42.345
Kate, have you...

51:42.347 --> 51:44.014
read <i>Persuasion?</i>

51:48.385 --> 51:49.886
What?

51:49.888 --> 51:50.887
By Jane Austen.

51:50.889 --> 51:53.456
I know who it's by.

51:53.458 --> 51:55.859
Yeah, it's, um...

51:55.861 --> 51:56.994
It's my favorite book.

51:56.996 --> 51:59.229
Why...? Why did you bring
something like that up?

51:59.231 --> 52:00.530
What made you bring that up?

52:00.532 --> 52:02.532
I just... A friend of mine
gave it to me recently,

52:02.534 --> 52:07.303
and I was wondering...
what it's about.

52:09.507 --> 52:11.808
It's... It's wonderful.

52:11.810 --> 52:13.543
Yeah.
Yeah.

52:13.545 --> 52:16.613
It's about, um...

52:16.615 --> 52:17.614
About waiting.

52:17.616 --> 52:19.516
(CHUCKLES)

