58:45.802 --> 58:49.039
MORGAN:
Kate.

58:49.041 --> 58:51.841
Hey, um... Alex was, uh...

58:51.843 --> 58:55.345
Alex was just telling me
about the, um... The lake house.

58:56.680 --> 58:58.381
Yeah, it sounds...
Sounds really great.

58:58.383 --> 59:00.216
Great.

59:01.785 --> 59:03.786
Alex, it's late.

59:05.222 --> 59:06.689
Yeah.

59:07.425 --> 59:08.658
Yeah. Um...

59:09.626 --> 59:11.561
Good night.
Good night.

59:26.227 --> 59:27.427
KATE:
<i>It was you.</i>

59:27.429 --> 59:29.996
WOMAN:
Do you work tomorrow night?

59:29.998 --> 59:32.132
Why didn't you say anything?

59:32.134 --> 59:36.269
ALEX: <i>You would've thought
I was crazy or drunk. Or both.</i>

59:36.271 --> 59:38.771
Yeah, but...

59:38.773 --> 59:41.374
I liked you.
You should have said something.

59:41.376 --> 59:44.444
How? You were
with your boyfriend.

59:44.446 --> 59:46.146
You know what?
Excuses, excuses.

59:46.148 --> 59:47.547
You are a coward.

59:47.549 --> 59:49.649
I'm not a coward.

59:49.651 --> 59:54.054
Oh, really? Well,
what about your girlfriend?

59:54.056 --> 59:56.122
What? I told you already,

59:56.124 --> 59:57.190
she's not my girlfriend.

59:57.192 --> 59:59.492
He's not my boyfriend either.

59:59.494 --> 01:00:01.661
Oh, really?
Well, what is he, then?

01:00:01.663 --> 01:00:03.096
Your brother?

01:00:03.098 --> 01:00:05.298
Ah. We have a comedian.

01:00:05.300 --> 01:00:08.501
<i>What'd you have, a clown</i>
<i>for breakfast this morning?</i>

01:00:10.637 --> 01:00:12.905
Wonderful. Our first fight.

01:00:12.907 --> 01:00:15.508
You could write a song about it
and go sing it in San Francisco.

01:00:15.510 --> 01:00:17.643
(PHONE RINGING)

01:00:21.148 --> 01:00:23.316
What?

01:00:23.318 --> 01:00:24.984
Hello.

01:00:24.986 --> 01:00:26.286
Hey, Henry.

01:00:28.355 --> 01:00:29.789
What?

01:00:29.791 --> 01:00:31.924
MAN:
You'll let me know, right?

01:00:31.926 --> 01:00:33.359
WOMAN:
Yes, I will.

01:00:35.062 --> 01:00:36.296
Hi.
Good afternoon.

01:00:36.298 --> 01:00:37.430
I'm looking for my father.

01:00:37.432 --> 01:00:38.798
I don't know
which room he's in.

01:00:38.800 --> 01:00:40.233
Simon Wyler?

01:00:40.235 --> 01:00:41.701
Mr. Wyler, the architect?

01:00:41.703 --> 01:00:43.236
Yes.

01:00:43.238 --> 01:00:44.237
I'm Anna Klyczynski.

01:00:44.239 --> 01:00:46.573
I'm the Attending
for your father.

01:00:46.575 --> 01:00:48.941
Hey. What happened?
How is he?

01:00:48.943 --> 01:00:51.177
He's okay. He's had
a heart attack.

01:00:51.179 --> 01:00:53.546
Fortunately, relatively minor.

01:00:53.548 --> 01:00:56.949
His vitals are fine,
and he's stable,

01:00:56.951 --> 01:00:59.352
but it will require
an intervention.

01:00:59.354 --> 01:01:01.988
He's agreed to schedule it
for tomorrow.

01:01:08.429 --> 01:01:10.930
(MACHINE BEEPING)

01:01:17.404 --> 01:01:19.539
Good to see
you're taking it easy.

01:01:20.907 --> 01:01:22.908
Well, you...
You didn't need to come.

01:01:22.910 --> 01:01:25.345
I'm perfectly well.

01:01:25.347 --> 01:01:27.614
Perfectly all right.

01:01:27.616 --> 01:01:30.250
Well, you had
a heart attack, Dad.

01:01:30.252 --> 01:01:33.786
I had an episode,
for chrissake.

01:01:33.788 --> 01:01:36.422
Nothing more.

01:01:36.424 --> 01:01:39.359
Appreciate it if you kept
everything in its perspective.

01:01:41.895 --> 01:01:43.463
Well, then, I just wanna
let you know

01:01:43.465 --> 01:01:44.930
I'm here if you need anything.

01:01:47.501 --> 01:01:49.735
Coffee.

01:01:49.737 --> 01:01:51.871
What?

01:01:51.873 --> 01:01:53.139
You heard me.

01:01:56.076 --> 01:01:57.277
Coffee.

01:01:59.746 --> 01:02:02.081
ALEX: <i>There's something
I never told you, Kate.</i>

01:02:02.083 --> 01:02:04.884
<i>You see, it was my father</i>
<i>who built the lake house.</i>

01:02:04.886 --> 01:02:08.120
<i>I mean, with his own hands.</i>

01:02:08.122 --> 01:02:11.157
<i>And it was a long time ago,</i>
<i>before he was famous,</i>

01:02:11.159 --> 01:02:14.594
<i>when he still had a family</i>
<i>and worshipped my mother.</i>

01:02:14.596 --> 01:02:15.895
<i>Her name was Mary,</i>

01:02:15.897 --> 01:02:18.598
<i>and the house was a gift</i>
<i>for her.</i>

01:02:18.600 --> 01:02:21.501
<i>She was smart and funny.</i>

01:02:21.503 --> 01:02:22.735
<i>She could've done anything,</i>

01:02:22.737 --> 01:02:25.305
<i>but chose to take care</i>
<i>of my brother and I</i>

01:02:25.307 --> 01:02:27.507
<i>and help him build his career.</i>

01:02:27.509 --> 01:02:29.209
<i>You see, the more successful</i>
<i>he became,</i>

01:02:29.211 --> 01:02:31.578
<i>the more impossible he was</i>
<i>to live with.</i>

01:02:31.580 --> 01:02:35.548
<i>Finally, she just couldn't take</i>
<i>living with him anymore.</i>

01:02:35.550 --> 01:02:38.685
<i>She left him.</i>

01:02:38.687 --> 01:02:41.020
<i>Within a year, she got sick.</i>

01:02:41.022 --> 01:02:45.925
<i>Unfortunately, she never</i>
<i>learned how to stop loving him.</i>

01:02:45.927 --> 01:02:49.662
<i>He wasn't at the funeral.</i>

01:02:49.664 --> 01:02:51.497
<i>When I asked him why...</i>

01:02:57.571 --> 01:03:00.039
Go on, Alex.
What did he say?

01:03:04.445 --> 01:03:05.545
He said, "She was dead to me

01:03:05.547 --> 01:03:07.747
the moment she stepped
out of the house."

01:03:11.184 --> 01:03:12.184
And then he gave me

01:03:12.186 --> 01:03:15.020
one of his
architect-of-the-year grins.

01:03:30.487 --> 01:03:31.988
I hope you appreciate this.

01:03:31.990 --> 01:03:34.958
I had to sneak past
three nurses and your Attending.

01:03:34.960 --> 01:03:37.593
Oh, jeez, it's hot.

01:03:37.595 --> 01:03:39.195
It's not decaf, is it?

01:03:39.197 --> 01:03:40.930
It should be, but it isn't.

01:03:40.932 --> 01:03:44.868
Ah... Mm.

01:03:44.870 --> 01:03:47.603
That's not bad.
Thank you...

01:03:47.605 --> 01:03:49.472
son.

01:03:49.474 --> 01:03:50.473
You're welcome.

01:03:50.475 --> 01:03:52.642
Where's your brother?

01:03:52.644 --> 01:03:55.078
I sent him away.
He wasn't feeling well.

01:03:55.080 --> 01:03:56.946
You know how he is.
He worries.

01:03:56.948 --> 01:03:58.181
Yeah, I know.

01:03:58.183 --> 01:04:00.383
He gets that from your mother,
I'm afraid.

01:04:00.385 --> 01:04:02.719
She always worried too much.

01:04:02.721 --> 01:04:04.154
What are you looking at?

01:04:04.156 --> 01:04:05.155
Hm?

01:04:05.157 --> 01:04:07.157
Oh, yeah, here, take a gander.

01:04:07.159 --> 01:04:10.359
It's a proposal for a museum.

01:04:10.361 --> 01:04:11.895
Who is it?

01:04:11.897 --> 01:04:14.831
Oh, someone new.

01:04:14.833 --> 01:04:18.334
Oh, I like the walkways,
where the light falls.

01:04:18.336 --> 01:04:20.103
What are the materials?

01:04:20.105 --> 01:04:22.572
Granite. Aluminum.

01:04:22.574 --> 01:04:25.075
White panels
are straight out of Meier,

01:04:25.077 --> 01:04:27.543
but the interior color coming
through the front windows,

01:04:27.545 --> 01:04:30.413
that's different.

01:04:30.415 --> 01:04:33.983
It's not new,
but it's clean, uncluttered.

01:04:33.985 --> 01:04:35.852
I like it.

01:04:35.854 --> 01:04:39.322
When was the last time
you were in Barcelona?

01:04:41.092 --> 01:04:43.760
Years ago, with you,
Mom and Henry.

01:04:43.762 --> 01:04:46.495
Do you remember visiting
Casa de la Caritat?

01:04:47.564 --> 01:04:49.398
The almshouse.
Mm-hm.

01:04:49.400 --> 01:04:52.068
That's right.
You mentioned Meier.

01:04:52.070 --> 01:04:54.904
His Barcelona museum
stands in the same area

01:04:54.906 --> 01:04:57.173
as Casa de la Caritat.

01:04:57.175 --> 01:04:59.375
It drinks the same light.

01:04:59.377 --> 01:05:03.046
Meier designed
a series of louvered skylights

01:05:03.048 --> 01:05:04.513
to capture that light

01:05:04.515 --> 01:05:07.617
and cast it inward
to illuminate the art within,

01:05:07.619 --> 01:05:09.518
but indirectly.

01:05:09.520 --> 01:05:10.754
And that was important,

01:05:10.756 --> 01:05:14.323
because although light
enhances art,

01:05:14.325 --> 01:05:16.059
it can also degrade it.

01:05:16.061 --> 01:05:18.561
But you know all that already,
you son of a...

01:05:18.563 --> 01:05:19.662
(CHUCKLES)

01:05:19.664 --> 01:05:20.830
Now, this...

01:05:20.832 --> 01:05:23.532
(COUGHS)

01:05:23.534 --> 01:05:25.701
where do you suppose
this is to be built?

01:05:25.703 --> 01:05:26.936
I have no idea.

01:05:26.938 --> 01:05:28.271
Oh, but you said you liked it.

01:05:28.273 --> 01:05:29.538
Conceptually.

01:05:29.540 --> 01:05:32.041
Now, come on.

01:05:32.043 --> 01:05:34.744
You know as well as I do
that the light in Barcelona

01:05:34.746 --> 01:05:37.446
is quite different
from the light in Tokyo.

01:05:37.448 --> 01:05:40.750
And the light in Tokyo is
different from that in Prague.

01:05:40.752 --> 01:05:42.986
A truly great structure,

01:05:42.988 --> 01:05:46.956
one that is meant
to stand the tests of time,

01:05:46.958 --> 01:05:49.659
never disregards
its environment.

01:05:49.661 --> 01:05:51.661
A serious architect
takes that into account.

01:05:51.663 --> 01:05:53.629
He knows
that if he wants presence,

01:05:53.631 --> 01:05:56.599
he must consult with nature.

01:05:56.601 --> 01:05:58.968
He must be captivated

01:05:58.970 --> 01:06:01.137
by the light.

01:06:01.139 --> 01:06:04.573
Always the light.
Always.

01:06:04.575 --> 01:06:06.609
(♪)

01:07:00.497 --> 01:07:02.932
Hey. I have an emergency.
Take my shift. Please.

01:07:02.934 --> 01:07:04.934
(PHONE RINGING)

01:07:07.804 --> 01:07:09.172
Hello.

01:07:09.174 --> 01:07:10.673
KLYCZYNSKI:
<i>Mr. Wyler?</i>

01:07:10.675 --> 01:07:12.375
Yes.

01:07:12.377 --> 01:07:15.745
<i>This is Dr. Klyczynski</i>
<i>at Chicago City Hospital.</i>

01:07:15.747 --> 01:07:19.515
<i>I'm afraid I have some</i>
<i>difficult news for you.</i>

01:07:22.619 --> 01:07:25.188
KATE:
<i>I'm so sorry, Alex.</i>

01:07:26.423 --> 01:07:30.059
<i>I wish somehow</i>
<i>I could be there with you,</i>

01:07:30.061 --> 01:07:31.494
<i>that we could sit together</i>

01:07:31.496 --> 01:07:33.997
<i>and look out over the water</i>
<i>and the light</i>

01:07:33.999 --> 01:07:36.900
<i>in this house</i>
<i>your father built.</i>

01:07:39.870 --> 01:07:43.006
<i>I could be a shoulder for you</i>
<i>like you've been for me.</i>

01:07:43.008 --> 01:07:46.142
<i>And tell you that</i>
<i>everything is gonna be okay.</i>

01:07:48.045 --> 01:07:51.080
<i>If I could do one thing</i>
<i>for you today,</i>

01:07:51.082 --> 01:07:53.349
<i>from here,</i>

01:07:53.351 --> 01:07:57.320
<i>one small, simple thing</i>
<i>from the future,</i>

01:07:57.322 --> 01:08:01.024
<i>I hope this is it.</i>

01:08:01.026 --> 01:08:02.892
<i>It won't be published</i>
<i>for a couple of years,</i>

01:08:02.894 --> 01:08:06.562
<i>but I don't think you should</i>
<i>have to wait that long.</i>

01:08:08.265 --> 01:08:10.566
<i>I hope it helps you know</i>
<i>how much you were loved.</i>

01:08:20.844 --> 01:08:22.745
(SIGHS)

01:08:53.777 --> 01:08:55.111
Aw.

01:08:55.113 --> 01:08:56.446
(SNIFFLES)

01:08:59.216 --> 01:09:00.883
(SIGHS)

01:09:07.924 --> 01:09:10.493
(SOBBING)

01:09:24.108 --> 01:09:26.075
